reviews.title: Top food and pleasant ambiance
reviews.text:
Had dinner here several times. Never been disappointing.

Top quality food. Friendly service and friendly staff. Wine list with options for everyone. From Willem's favorites to Romanée-conti.

Recommended for lovers of fine dining.

reviews.title: Enjoy with a big G
reviews.text:
Fantastic dishes, delicious fine flavors. A surprise 4 course menu Great service.
a great night out. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Perfection!
reviews.text:
Beautiful evening, with very nice dishes, special ambiance and excellent service.
Fine and very good hostess and host.
Greetings,
Hans de Vries

reviews.title: One of my best dining experiences ever
reviews.text: Great food and service. I also visited other renowned restaurants like Joann (Enschede) and the Nieuwe Winkel (Nijmegen) during the same period, but I really liked this better. Dishes look beautiful, but it was also really tasty. The service was friendly and you sit in a beautiful ambiance. One of my best eating experiences.

reviews.title: Hip & Chic
reviews.text:
The restaurant is located in the very center of Borne in a magnificent building from the turn of the century. 

There are plenty of parking spaces.

The entire interior is a dream and was probably very expensive.

In the "Dutch Michelin" > Lekker 2024 it is not among the first 100 restaurants in the Netherlands.

To be brief: 
Our overall impression: hip & chic! 

What is now a thing of the past in many comparable restaurants ... is consistently maintained here: 
Tiny, interesting and very elaborately prepared portions. 

Conclusion: 
The main course (cod) contained a portion the size of half a matchbox.

reviews.title: Just on a Thursday evening
reviews.text: Dorset's spring offer was irresistible. It had been a while since we had eaten in Borne and we were looking forward to it. We sat down for an all-inclusive 5-course menu at 6 p.m. Only 5 occupied tables this evening. A restaurant like Dorset really deserves more. Although the Dutchman Nico de Haan, known in ornithological circles, was also there. And no, he didn't eat guinea fowl. We start with two delicious oysters and a glass of bubbles. Delicious with that Oriental infusion. One appetizer. That could have been a little more generous. But very tasty. Then we start with a variation on a steak tartare. And we can safely say that it was a very successful one. Then a piece of beautifully finished eel. A nice subtle dish. We notice that the kitchen brigade is not afraid and dares to cook with high taste. A spicy bite is not avoided. Kudos! We continue with a beautifully al dente piece of cod, which also turns out to be surprisingly spicy. The main course was a deliciously tender piece of roe. To conclude, a dessert that was not just sweet, but contained delicious flavor notes of various herbs. Finish with a cup of espresso and of course the lukewarm Dorset macaroons, which have been served for many years. We enjoyed it again.

reviews.title: Fantastic experience
reviews.text: Restaurant Dorset is an all-time favorite. Great location, beautiful and cozy interior, nice casual group of guests and a fantastic team of people. In Dorset you don't eat in a restaurant but with a family. Warm welcome at the door, casual way of hospitality and before you know it you are sitting at the kitchen table where you meet not only the kitchen family but also other guests. The food is finished. From the appetizer through a whole series of culinary parties (dishes are not enough) to the sweet climax with coffee. This is a place where you want to celebrate. Even if it is life itself. Top top top. Go here!

reviews.title: Surprising! Enjoyed
reviews.text: We had a very delicious meal here. Time and time again we were surprised by the dishes. The service was very friendly and the chef also came to the table. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Beautiful
reviews.text: Absolutely lovely. Great wines and a small but beautiful selection of dishes, which are a treat to both the taste buds and the eyes. Not big eaters, so their small dishes were perfect although we added one plate of fries to share.

reviews.title: All correct, not up to the expected level
reviews.text:
Went there with my colleagues for our Christmas dinner. 
The decoration of the place is very nice and ostentatious. 
We were received with a welcome cocktail and then had a five course meal. 
Every place was nicely prepared and decorated and the ingredients of excellent quality. Nevertheless, I did not get the impression that I was having the meal of my life and the combination of ingredients was in some cases not really well balanced: one of the plates was a ceviche that lacked acidity and power; the beef sirloin was lacking some sauce and combined with dill and celery that were really overpowering and took away all that nice flavor. I like the opportunity to get into the kitchen and meet the chef to taste the “same h watch out with the spicy cauliflower that happened to lack the kick. 
These comments come because those kinds of mistakes are not aligned with the high price of the meal they are asking for, not because the food is bad... which indeed is not!
Great location for a romantic quiet evening or for an evening business dinner. 
I recommend it, although there is some room for improvement.

reviews.title: Hihg-end food and wine
reviews.text: We had a 'surprise' 5 course dinner, with good fish, well prepared veal and very good desert. And matching wine from the friendly staff. Not cheap, but money well spent.

reviews.title: Nice restaurant
reviews.text:
Had dinner at this restaurant with my wife. Ambiance is good and price for 3 course mail is cheap.
Wine list was a bit dissapointing. A lot of spanish red wine and not enough good italian or french options. For example one of the most expensive reds is a chateau Cheval bl 1996. That wasn’t a good vintage and it’s peak was in 2015/2016.

reviews.title: Great meal
reviews.text:
We go here once a year with a special deal.  3 course meal with optional additions.
This time we did one addition, it seemed very skimpy and was not what we expected.  Next time I will ask about it because for 12 bucks it seems steep!
Black Angus was Amazing!! the best part of the entire meal!  They also have a very nice selection whiskies!

reviews.title: Family diner
reviews.text: Went tonight for diner with family to Dorset.  It's a nice location. The staff was friendly. We had an English guest, they did there best to translate the menu and explain the food. We had a 4 dishes surprising menu with wine tasting. It was really delicious. Would go again!

reviews.title: The locals may think it's great but there's not too much to write home about
reviews.text: I understand that for the 'locals' this might be a good restaurant but in the grand scheme of things (for anybody that has travelled) the food is just above average. The service is OK - although my husband was offered a second aperatif and I was totally ignored (shock horror!!).  There were 3 couples eating in the restaurant this evening plus a table of 26.  We were the last couple to be seated (next to the 26) and the noise they made gave me a headache.  There was another part of the restaurant that was totally empty, where management could have seated us and we may have enjoyed the evening a little bit more. In short....a restaurant that thinks it is better than it actually is.  The food is acceptable but for the prices they ask we would have expected something a little better.  Will not be going there again - but that is our choice.................

reviews.title: Very nice spot
reviews.text:
We went here with a deal of 'couples dinner'.  Basically, it was buy one get one.  Dinner was very nice!  The mansion is beautiful!  Lots of history in it!
Staff was very helpful and offered often.  I will include some pics, but it was VERY dark in the restaurant, so I had to brighten the photos which made them kinda grainy.
We did the 4 course dinner.  
First was shrimp, scallops and some trimmings.  Not much to eat, but it was a starter.
Second was sea bass.  Very tasty!
Third was Duck (main course).  I found it very chewy and wound up pulling tendons out to be able to eat it.  I was hoping for a cut of beef, but oh well....
Lastly, we has dessert which was a thick slice of pineapple with sorbet and other nice things on top.
For coffee, they gave us a very nice selection of cookies and other sweets.
Was a very nice experience!

reviews.title: This is what a perfect night out should be!
reviews.text: Great staff, superb food, great ambiance, all together you really feel spoiled and pampered! If you are in the neighbourhood, this is the place you should visit. It has a rare combination; fancy and and the same time laid-back.

reviews.title: Perfect Restaurant
reviews.text:
We have spent the last 4 years a few times at Dorset.
And each visit was worth it.

We always take the surprise menu with matching wines.
And every time the food is great and the accompanying wine makes the food taste even better.
The wine is nicely presented you. They are not difficult with the wine and leave it on the table. So you can pour an extra glass itself.

The atmosphere is very good. You can first warm up by the fireplace with an appetizer. The restaurant is filled with tables so you have plenty of space and privacy.

All in all a perfect restaurant to eat more often.

reviews.title: Quality packed experience
reviews.text:
We visited Dorset Restaurant for the second time a few weeks ago, this time during a (national) action discount week. And while some of the restaurants that participate in this action adjust their quality and service Dorset keep up their high standards. Just like our first visit (with 2 persons) we were got a warm and friendly welcome, the staff stayed attentive and 'on the job' for the rest of the evening without being to present. They offered a special action menu which was still of a very high quality and a beautiful presentation as always. And the chef had as much inspiration and enthousiasm as offered 'a la carte'.
If you are looking for a great place to have a dinner-night-out keep Dorset in mind!
